The gubernatorial candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP in Jigawa State, Mustapha Sule Lamido has reiterated the fact that his being youthful gives him a greater advantage with the strength and the mental alertness needed for the task of taking Jigawa to the next level. He spoke on Friday after the party formally received the former Deputy Governor Ahmed Mahmoud back to its fold at an event held in Bamaina. The opposition parties have been latching on to his youthfulness to whip up sentiments that he lacked the requisite experience. While insisting that his age is not an issue but the ability to deliver on all expectations, saying that his knowledge and experience would give him the opportunity to provide solutions to most of the hardships brought on citizens by the APC administration. “My young age is my strength and would give me the determination to bring a proper solution to the problems bedevilling the state. ”This is an opportunity for people at a young age to come together and support the PDP to fix the country.” He assured that more people would soon join the party and also promised equal treatment to new members of the party. 